    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="330"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1451a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="6" xml:id="d330fn6">Same to American Consul at Puerto Plata.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President will shortly propose a plan for the restoration of peace and
                    establishment of order in Santo Domingo. Meantime he asks that hostilities be
                    suspended until the proposition can be laid before Santo Domingo.</p>
                <pb facs="0363" n="247" xml:id="pg_247"/>
                <p>Please communicate this to the Foreign Office and to all participants who can be
                    reached directly or indirectly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
